Gruta Changelog
===============

 Gruta - Hierarchical Notepad (+CGI)
 Copyright (C) 2001/2002 Angel Ortega <angel@triptico.com>
 Home Page: http://www.triptico.com/

0.7 - sáb mar 22 12:55:38 CET 2003
----------------------------------

 - A very big change; there is no stinkin' configuration file.
   Config data is stored inside the datafile itself. From now,
   the datafiles are executable CGIs, with a first line of

   #!/usr/bin/perl /path/to/gruta

0.4beta4 - vie feb 22 18:22:15 CET 2002
---------------------------------------

 - New parameter to limit the size of a POST.

0.4beta3 - mar feb 19 21:17:01 CET 2002
---------------------------------------

 - Minor change in grutatxt: the main grutatxt() function
   now recieves a hash of options instead of a scalar.

 - More changes to grutatxt: new option, class-oddeven,
   to generate odd-even classes to tables.

0.4beta2
--------

 - Important fix: if Gruta is set as the default handler
   in httpd, the SCRIPT_NAME cannot be used for the
   options, as all would appear to be the same; now the
   REQUEST_URI (stripped from its parameters) is used.
   This can cause problems if Gruta is not a default
   handler, I've not tested it; more web browsers should
   be tested as well (Mozilla and Netscape on Linux seems
   to work).

 - More text processing 'marks' (* for bold, _ for cursive
   and definition lists).

 - New 'Cancel' button in New, Edit and Delete operations.

0.4beta
-------

 - Big change: there is now only one configuration
   file, with several profiles classified by its REQUEST_URI.

0.3.15beta - jue ene 24 20:41:19 CET 2002
-----------------------------------------

 - Version and mtime of the element being edited are
   written as HTML comments.

0.3.14beta - sáb ene  5 01:13:05 CET 2002
-----------------------------------------

 - New 'wikifying' of function names.

0.3.13beta - lun dic  3 21:51:06 CET 2001
-----------------------------------------

 - Datafile locking via an ordinary .lck file.

0.3.11beta - dom sep 30 17:19:39 CEST 2001
------------------------------------------

 - Calendaring functions (date filtering with repetitions).

 - css CGI parameter is not inherited.

0.3.10beta - sáb sep 29 13:23:19 CEST 2001
------------------------------------------

 - Corrected a bug that prevented to add more than one
   'unnamed' elements to root.

 - New configuration parameter, root_text, to include
   any raw HTML text to be always included just below the
   Gruta element path.

0.3.9beta - dom sep  9 17:24:59 CEST 2001
-----------------------------------------

 - Element command disposition has changed.

 - New 'new' command in every element (almost the same as the
   below 'new' command, but setting current element as root).

0.3.8 - vie sep  7 20:47:22 CEST 2001
-------------------------------------

 - The elements are locked when being edited.

0.3.8beta - lun sep  3 21:43:36 CEST 2001
-----------------------------------------

 - New 'sync' and 'merge' commands.

0.3.7 - lun sep  3 20:50:20 CEST 2001
-------------------------------------

 - New 'store' command, to receive a remote Gruta database.

 - New 'admin' command, that allows to call the 'store',
   'sync', 'merge' and 'dump' commands easily.

0.3.6 - vie ago 31 15:31:05 CEST 2001
-------------------------------------

 - New 'raw' command, to show a page suitable for been
   converted to text (using lynx's or links' -dump mode).

 - The generated HTML is more correct in unsorted lists.

 - Ordered lists ala wiki are now supported.

0.3.5 - jue ago 23 12:52:03 CEST 2001
-------------------------------------

 - Confirmation when deleting elements.

 - The 'Set as root' command has been isolated from the
   'Edit' and 'Del' commands to prevent accidental deletions.

 - The 'Parent node' selection list now shows the nodes
   hyerarchically indented.
